***** DIVS AND SPANS *****


- Divs and spans are just generic boxes that can contain other elements.
- Often times, these elements are used to be "hook" elements.
- We can give an id or class to target them for styling with CSS.

- Another use case regularly faced is grouping related elements under one parent element to correctly position them on the page.

- Div
    - Used as a container element to group other elements.
    - <div> is a block-level element by default.
    - Allow us to divide the page into different blocks and apply styling to these blocks.

- Span
    - Can be used to group text content and inline HTML elements for styling.
    - <span> is an inline-level element by default
    - Should be used when no other semantic HTML element is appropriate.
